    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909417>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10 Phylogeny of the ’Splendeuptychia clade’ based on the FULL dataset. Interpretation of support values can be found in the legend. The scale bars under the butterfly images equal 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909417/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909497>
    dc:description "FIGURE 37 Modica confusa comb.n. (a) male wing venation; (b and c) male (FLMNH-MGCL-269550) dorsal (b) and ventral (c); (d and e) female dorsal (d) and ventral (e). Scale bars 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909497/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909501>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38 Modica gen.n. representative species. (a) M. myncea comb.n (neotype); (b) M. fugitiva comb.n (neotype); (c) M. maripa comb.n (MB-1708-13); (d) M. kamel comb.n (KW-081111-67). Scale bars 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909501/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909503>
    dc:description "FIGURE 39 Modica confusa comb.n. (a–d) male genitalia (dissection KW-21-64), lateral (a) with posterior view juxta, dorsal (b), aedeagus lateral (c) and aedeagus dorsal (d); (e–h) female genitalia (dissection KW-21-65), lateral view exterior tip abdomen (e), ventral view exterior tip abdomen (f), dorsal view interior abdomen (g), corpus bursae perpendicular to signa (h). Scale bars 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909503/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7909507>
    dc:description "FIGURE 40 Modica gen.n. Species diversity mapped on a 2 degree grid. Colours ranging from dark green to red represent increasing diversity." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7909507/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

